The paper proposes a new heuristic distributed architecture for deep reinforcement learning (DRL) algorithm, which involves using multiple agents for parallel training and a PSO based network update mechanism. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
